agents.name: Purge Star Wars Fast Ship Report
agents.description:
Clear a resource value in Tines.

Link to API documentation: https://www.tines.com/api/resources/update

local.final_payload:
=REJECT(
  LOCAL.all_parameters,
  LAMBDA(
    item,
    OR(
      item = NULL,
      IF(
        OR(
          TYPE(item) = "TrueClass",
          TYPE(item) = "FalseClass",
          TYPE(item) = "Integer"
        ),
        IS_EMPTY(TEXT(item)),
        IS_EMPTY(item)
      )
    )
  )
)

options.guidance: Output every object that has a hyperdrive_rating of 1.0
Write a summary of how many objects along with their hyperdrive_rating
Write a summary of each object along with the hyperdrive_rating
options.script:
from typing import List, Dict

def main(input: List[Dict[str, str]]) -> List[Dict[str, str]]:
    result = []
    for obj in input:
        name = obj.get('name')
        model = obj.get('model')
        hyperdrive_rating = obj.get('hyperdrive_rating')
        summary = f"The {name} is a {model} with a hyperdrive rating of {hyperdrive_rating}."
        result.append({'summary': summary})
    return result

diagram_notes.content: # Exercise 1 - Choose another Star Wars API Endpoint to create a similar workflow or a workflow of your choice.  You can copy the workflow from the first training session, Episode IV.

# Requirements
-  Create a Tines Resouce called Fast_Ship_Results, Slow_Ship_Results,  and  two Stars Wars Ship file names.

# Tines Documentation
-  [Tines WHERE Function](https://www.tines.com/docs/formulas/functions/where/)
- [Tines FILTER Function](https://www.tines.com/docs/formulas/functions/filter/)
- [Tines INCLUDES Function](https://www.tines.com/docs/formulas/functions/includes/)
- [Tines OBJECT function](https://www.tines.com/docs/formulas/functions/object/)
- [Tines OBJECTS_TO_CSV Function](https://www.tines.com/docs/formulas/functions/objects-to-csv/)
- [Tines CONCAT Function](https://www.tines.com/docs/formulas/functions/concat/)
- [Tines DATE Function](https://www.tines.com/docs/formulas/functions/date/)
- [Tines Resources](https://www.tines.com/docs/resources/)
- [Tines Implode Mode](https://www.tines.com/docs/actions/types/event-transformation/implode/)

# Goals
- Learn how to use AI Automatic Mode for Event Transformations for filtering data.
- Learn the WHERE, FILTER, and INCLUDES Tines Functions for filtering data.
- Dive deeper into Tines Resources by writing to a Tines Resource.
- Learn the Implode Mode for Event Transformation.
- Learn how to create a csv report that contains filtered data using the OBJECT Function.
These Tines action insert a blank array into the report resource so they can be reused in future reports.

- Where function  & Filter Function vs. AI Automatic Mode
- Advanced Mode for Troubleshooting
# ****Start Here - 2****  Learning how to slice and dice  data with event transformations
# Exercise 2 - Choose another Star Wars API Endpoint to create two arrays in a Tines Resource so you can practice filtering data using different Tines Functions and the AI Automatic Mode
